    "reasoning": "To implement the TopModule, we need to create an 8-bit edge detector circuit. Each bit of the input 'in' must be monitored for transitions (from 0 to 1 or 1 to 0). The output 'anyedge' should be set to 1 the cycle after such a transition occurs. This requires storing the previous value of each bit and comparing it with the current value. If they differ, we assert the corresponding bit in 'anyedge'. Since this needs to be done for each of the 8 bits independently, we'll use 8 separate flip-flops to store previous values, and combinational logic to detect the transitions. We will use logic type for all signals and use always @(posedge clk) for the sequential behavior. Each bit's detection is handled independently by using the same logic structure for all 8 bits. Also, since this is edge detection, we want to assert the output after detecting the change, hence we store the previous value and compare.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input [7:0] in,\n    output [7:0] anyedge\n);\n\n    // Register to store previous input values\n    logic [7:0] prev_in;\n\n    // Detect edges for each bit\n    logic [7:0] edges;\n\n    // Sequential logic to store previous input\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        prev_in <= in;\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic to detect edges\n    always @(*) begin\n        edges = in ^ prev_in;\n    end\n\n    // Output is asserted one cycle after edge is detected\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        anyedge <= edges;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
